        "detailed_description": {
            "textblock": "This study aims to study 80 patients with comorbid alcohol dependence and a depressive\n      syndrome.  After appropriate detoxification, patients are started on either naltrexone 50 mg\n      or placebo.  After one week, sertraline is added in an open label fashion.  It is\n      hypothesized that those patients receiving combination therapy will last 3 months with\n      follow-up tracking lasting 1 year."
        }, 
        "eligibility": {
